inn1.comm: full, on off, hits the outside half of the bat
length ball, defended back to him
down the wicket, not quite to the pitch of the ball, defends it back
goes back to cut, but it is not short enough, and is beaten
flighted outside off, defended to cover
flighted on middle and leg, defended
swinging away from Smith, left alone
full and on off, driven to mid-off
short of a length, on off, seams away, beats Smith's edge, reaches Akmal head high
short of a length, outside off, left alone
full, angling in, pushed wide of square leg, but somehow they decide against the single
full and straight, driven back to him. We have had back-to-back maidens now
Charles backs away to make room, Hafeez follows him, and draws a dot
makes room again, but he can't beat short cover
short of a length, played off the back foot, but finds point
full and straight and flat. Defended to cover
topspinner, straight, defended back to him
finally a run. Driven wide of mid-on
full, fast, swinging, but down the leg side. Five wides
full again, clipped away off the toes for a couple square of long leg
length ball, angling away, left alone. Akmal collects it in front of his chest
that's a lucky boundary. Full outside off, nearly a yorker, and it goes off the inside edge to fine leg for four
short of a length, middle and leg, Charles wants to pull, and is beaten on the bottm edge
lovely shot. Length ball, on off, push-drives with an open face, between mid-off and cover
short of a length, just outside off, defended to cover
length ball, into the pads, worked away for a single
full, outside off, driven to mid-off
flighted just outside off, defended back to him
tossing it up to invite the drive, this time to cover
and here comes the arm ball, but it too far down leg, and is easily worked away for one
makes room to drive this to long-on for one
shortish, Charles tries to pull, and is again beaten on the bottom edge
dug in short this time, left alone outside off
bouncer, middle and leg, he tries a half-hearted pull. Beaten
on a length, but it rises enough to hit the thigh pad. Concedes a leg-bye
top-edged for a six. Smith is by no means in control of this hit, but it clears Junaid Khan at fine leg. He hooked this from head high
short of a length outside off, left alone
length ball, on off, defended back to him
full, pitched outside leg, driven to mid-on
short of a length, pitched outside leg again. Lucky to get away with it. The fine leg is up. Only the leg-bye conceded

and Smith does what he has become used to. Another single-figures score. Follows a wide length ball, away from the body, no feet. The ball moves away a touch, and takes the edge to second slip where he is caught by... well... Hafeez
short of a length, outside off, angling in, left alone
wide length ball, left alone. End of a wicket-maiden
length ball outside off, left alone. Extra bounce again
full and straight, middle and leg, pushed to mid-on
short of a length, outside off, angling away, beats him on the cut
length ball angling away, guided away to third man
short of a length, down the leg side, called a wide
short of a length, just outside off, defended off the back foot
full outside off, pushed to cover-point
backs away and heaves at a shortish delivery, gets a single to deep backward square
short of a length, outside off, defended with an open face to point
wide length ball, driven on the up, but can't beat cover
bouncer, wide outside off. Easy to avoind
wide length ball, driven on the up, to the right of cover. Superb back-foot drive
left alone outside off
short of a length, outside off. Spongy bounce beats the cut
bouncer, just outside off, drops his wrists under it
looks to cut a shortish ball, gets a thick top edge that reaches third man on a bounce. Junaid does well to get to his left to field. He seems to have hurt a finger on the left hand
beautiful drive. Wide half-volley, he stands tall, moves forward, and pushes it past cover
short of a length, rising into the chest. Fended
moves all the way across to a straight length ball, but seems to have got an inside edge to save him
short of a length, outside off, pushed to point
short of a length, outside off, pushed past point for one
length ball, on off, defended from the crease
full, on off, dug out into the leg side for one
bouncer, accurate too, and Bravo nicely drops his wrists under it. Sways out of the line too
short of a length, just outside off, runs off the outside half of the bat for one
short of a length, middle and leg, defended from the crease
length ball down the leg side, lucky to hit the pad on the way
this time he is further down the leg side
full outside off, driven nicely, but straight to cover
clipped away off the pad for one
wide length ball, driven on the up, but straight to cover
length ball, angling in, worked away to square leg
length ball, angling in, pushed to mid-on
short of a length, angling in, dabbed to point
not in control of the pull, but it bounces well short of deep square leg

appeal for catch at the wicket, not given and they have immediately reviewed it. And it's not just Junaid and Akmal, even Hafeez wants the review. Short of a length, angling in, Bravo is not behind the line as he defends. There is a clear sound as the ball passes the outside edge, but there is no obvious deviation. Bravo, a walker from whatever cricket I have seen him play, is not pleased with this. Seriously we don't have enough technology here to operate proper DRS. He has given him out based on sound alone. Bravo is left to shake his head
length ball, angling in, defended off the back foot
quick, angling in, hits the inside half of the bat
difficult chance grassed. Charles top-edges another pull shot, Ajmal has to run to his left from long leg, but the ball swerves away a little at the last moment, and his dive is not good enough
on a length, on off, defended back to him
wild wild heave. On a knee, in front of the stumps, goes hard at a wide length ball, and inside-edges it to fine leg
length ball, outside off, moves back and across to defend
wide length ball, pushed between point and cover-point for one
short of a length, outside off, square-driven, but not past the diving Shehzad at point
length ball, angling in, nicely clipped away past midwicket for a couple
short of a length, on off, Samuels moves back and across to defend
short of a length, angling in, played to square leg
bouncer, outside off, 136ks. Samuels stays away from its line
short again, but not quite a bouncer. Defended in front of off
short of a length, pitched outside leg, defended in front of leg
length ball, outside off, pushed between point and cover for one
fullish, angling in, Samuels still stays back and drives this to mid-on

dropped. Samuels stays back for another length hall, and this time ends up offering a return chance. However, the ball hits Asad's chest even before the hands come up. Always difficult to catch them in your follow-through
driven, but straight to cover
bouncer this time, pretty accurate too, Samuels sways out of its way
stays back to a length ball and defends
full, on off, pushed back to him
quick length ball, defended in front of off
quick and flat again, punched to long-off this time
flighted on off, Samuels is caught half-forward and defends
down the wicket to take this on the half-volley. Gets a single to long-on
fired in at 98ks, hits his pad, but angling down leg
stays back again, a length ball again, nearly played on, but it bounces over the stumps
moves half-forward this time. Defends
wide length ball, dabbed away to point
short of a length, outside off, steered away to third man
wide length ball, played with an open face to point
short of a length, just outside off, he opens the body and swipes this over wide mid-on for four
comes down the wicket to york himself. Manages to dig this out
leaves the crease again, beaten in flight again, but gets an inside edge to short fine leg
lovely shot. Afridi tosses this one up wide outside off, Charles ddacnes down the track, takes it on a half-volley, and goes inside-out over extra cover
short of a length, he rocks back to punch this to long-on

Samuels leaves the crease again, and this time he has smoked this on the half-volley. Hits the stumps at the non-striker's end, and bursts through for a single. Umpire Wilson must be thanking the stumps
flatter, shorter, cut away to deep point
Charles' charmed life continues. He is looking long-on, hitting third man. Backs away and swipes, gets a thickish edge from outside leg, and it goes wide of Umar Akmal
full, outside off, pushed to mid-off
moves inside the line to work this to long leg for one
full, swinging in, nearly a yorker. Dug out
backs away, Asad bowls a slower ball, Charles recovers well and drives it to the right of deep cover for two
full, pushed to short midwicket where Hafeez's fumble doesn't result in a singe
down the wicket again, hit in the air, but doesn't carry to long-on
flighted outside off, driven to long-off for one
Samuels refuses to stay in the crease when Afridi is bowling. He is beaten in the flight again, still goes ahead with the shot, slicing it wide of deep cover
finally he stays in the crease. Defends off the front foot
flat and fast, hits him on the pad as Samuels leaves his crease again
short of a length, flat, outside edge, Samuels stays in the crease, gets a bottom edge
length ball, on off, defended from the crease
short of a length, outside off, the spongy bounce beats his attempt to late-cut
beaten by a shortish delivery outside off again
short of a length, outside off, defended off the back foot
length ball outside off, left alone
length ball, pitched outside leg, Samuels gets inside the line to place it between deep square and deep midwicket
down the wicket again, Afridi bowls short of a length, punched to deep cover
flighted outside off, driven to short cover
Charles leaves this crease this time. Even he is beaten in flight, but he recovers well to punch this shrortish delivery to deep point
clipped to deep midwicket for a single
stays in the crease to open his face on a length ball. Finds short third man
swipes, is hit on the inside half if the bat by a full delivery
short of a length, outside off, beats him with the angle again
stays short of a length, fended with soft hands, towards gully. Keeps it down
opens the face again, but finds gully again
moves across the stumps to get inside the line, and takes a single to square leg
swipes eyes shut again, and is beaten by a short ball
bouncer, just outside off, just stands there and let it go
parallel six. For a moment, I thought he would long-off here because the ball had hardly left ground, but it kept travelling and travelling, defying gravity. He had charged down once again
dances down the wicket again, gets close to the ball, and drives him between the umpire and long-on for a whistling boundary all along the ground
length ball, on the pads, opens the face, takes the single
short of a length, outside off, punched to deep point
Samuels leaves the crease, is beaten by the dip on the ball, but has his pad ready as the second line of defence
tossed up on off, defended off the front foot
short of a length, dabbed away to backward point
slightly fuller than the previous delivery, Charles pushes at it, and is beaten by the angle

Charles' pained effort comes to an end with an awkward pull shot. That's head high and outside off, and he decides to pull it. There is no way anyone can control a hook  from that line and height. And this time the edge finds a fielder too
dug in short, rising towards the chest, fended down with both feet in the air
short and wide, cut away to the left of deep cover. Jamshed makes a diving save at the boundary
full and wide, nearly a yorker, beats Samuels
flighted outside off, played towards long-on off the inside half of the bat
flighted on middle and leg, driven to long-on
flat, on off, defended off the front foot
tossed up outside off, driven to long-off for one
tossed up, just outside off, defended off the back foot
appeal for lbw as this one breaks in and beats the inside edge, but it seems to have hit him outside the line of off. Not given. They discuss it, but don't review it
length ball outside off, left alone
short of a length, pitches middle and off, angling away, left alone
wide length ball, left alone
short of a length, pitches middle and leg, defended in front of off
short of a length, outside off, Gayle gets behind it and punches it to the left of cover
full, on off, defended solidly from the crease
quick offbreak, defended from the crease
short of a length, outside off, punched to deep cover
length ball, outside off, defended wide of cover
defended off the front foot
quick length ball, dabbed wide of short third man for a single
length ball angling in, worked behind square for one
length ball outside off, beats the inside edge on the drive
driven to mid-off
bouncer, 131ks, but accurate, Gayle sways out of its line
length ball, starts on off, left alone with the angle
length ball, on off, defended off the front foot
short, flat, beats him in the flight. Samuels defends to leg
short of a length, middle and leg, defended to leg
flat offbreak, into the pads, defended to leg
short of a length, middle and leg, defended
length ball, into the pads, defended to leg
short of a length, down the wicket, pushed to straight short midwicket
length ball, angling in, beats the inside edge, hits his pad, but outside the line of off
offbreak, on off, defended with an open face
flatter, quicker, beats the inside edge, but seems to be headed down leg
offbreak this time, breaks away from off to beat the outside edge. Extra bounce too
defended off the front foot
flatter, quicker offbreak. Gayle stays back, and is beaten by the turn
drives a length ball down the ground, but Afridi makes a diving save at mid-off
short of a length, angling in, punched away to deep point
short of a length, angling in, pushed to short midwicket
length ball, on off, defended from the crease
bouncer, middle and off, Gayle ducks under it
short of a length, nips back in to beat the inside edge, but it is headed down leg
short of a length, flat, beats the pull. Not short enough to pull
offbreak, shortish, goes off the pad to short fine leg
full, and fired down the leg side. Finally Gayle gets some space, and he has placed this past the diving short fine leg for his first runs in his last 18 balls
that is into the sea. Length ball, into the pads, and lofted over long-on
fired into the pads, played with one hand, to deep square
wants to go down the track, or just bluffs him with the front-foot movement. Hafeez drags this short, and Samuels rocks back to pull this through midwicket for four
short of a length, pushed to mid-off for a quick single, and Asad Ali's misfield allows them the second too
lovely one-handed catch by Akmal. Bouncer, higher than the shoulder, Gayle gets a top edge on the hook, and Akmal takes a leaping catch to his right. Gayle walks
length ball, angling in, defended form the crease
on a length, on off, holds its line a bit. Defended back to him
hits the inside half of the bat with a length ball
short of a length, angling in, dropped into the leg side for a single
flighted outside off, driven to mid-off
dabs this offbreak wide of point for one
moves across the line to work this towards deep midwicket for one
too short, "Nahi, Saeed bhai," shouts Akmal, and he is punched away through point for four
flighted on off, defended off the front foot
down the wicket, takes this on a half-volley, gets under it, and lofts it over long-off for a six
dug in short, makes room to cut it between cover and point

Safe. Samuels looks to back away, Junaid provides him no room, he ends up slicing it over the man from cover running back. Misbah it was. Afridi might have had a better chance running in from mid-off rather than Misbah running back from cover
Simmons moves across the stumps, is beaten on the inside edge, but it has angled down the leg side
length ball outside off, pushed to mid-off for a single
short ball, a little slow, beats his pull
nearly a yorker, sliced away to third man for one
good bouncer. Angling in, following his head. Simmons has to sway out of its line
quick offbreak, defended to leg
topspinner, just short of a length, played to midwicket
sharp offbreak, hits him on the pad, but it is headed down leg
short of a length, on off, pushed back to him
short of a length, gets inside the line, but can't beat square leg
maiden over in a Powerplay. Quick offbreak fired into the pads, and he is cramped and does nothing
short of a length, middle and off, angling away. Beaten
short of a length, on off, angling away, left alone
fuller now, middle and leg, defended from the crease
Simmons charges down the wicket, and just swipes at this short ball. The bottom edge goes nowhere. No run for 11 balls now
finally a run. Steered to third man for a single
full, just outside off, can't beat point with the drive
just after the maiden, Ajmal goes for a six first ball. The difference is the batsman on strike. It is Simmons now, who dances down the wicket to loft him over long-on
flighted on the pads, bunted around the corner for one
short of a length, punched to short cover
slower, dips on him, turns in, bounces a little, hits the high part of the defensive ball
flighted outside off, pushed to short cover again
Ajmal's last 10 balls to Samuels: zero runs. This is the doosra, hits the outside half of the bat, in front of middle and off
full and straight, driven to long-on for one

Samuels' struggle ends. A day after he said something to the effect of "I have this Pakistan attack sorted". Bouncer outside off, he has been under a lot of pressure for his strike rate, and just throws his bat at this. Ends up toe-ending and dragging it to long-on for a sharp low catch from Afridi
full and outside off, Simmons tries to open the face, and is beaten
low full toss outside off, dug out for a single past cover
short of a length, angling away, left alone by Bravo
superb delivery to end his quota. Short of a length, on off, seams away, and kicks away to beat the outside edge. His last five overs have gone for nine runs and have brought Pakistan two wickets
length ball, on the pads, worked away into the leg side
doosra, just outside off, defended from the crease
short of a length, turning in, he finds square leg with the bunt

another doosra. Possibly the topspinner. This didn't turn in for sure. Beat the outside edge. Squares him up. Bravo's back foot leaves the ground for a briefest moment, but is down by the time Akmal removes the bail
tossed up outside off, played against the turn, wide of long-off. Comes back for two
flatter offbreak, beats the inside edge, but hits him outside the line of off

that looks like lbw. Simmons goes across the line to try a paddle over short fine. Simmons is beaten. Caught dead plumb, but not given. Pakistan review it. The replays return an "umpire's call" on the leg stump. I am surprised, though. More than half the ball is hitting the leg stump
down the wicket, Ali bowls short, but Bravo goes ahead with the drive on the up, and beats deep point
swinging low full toss, beats the inside edge, but is headed down leg
yorker, superb yorker, on middle and off. Simmons can't do much with it
low full toss, mis-hit down the ground for a single
wide down the leg side. He seems to have got a touch on it, and doesn't even beat the keeper. Bowler lucky to get away with this one

Ajmal gets the man who has hit him for two sixes today. Simmons tries the slog sweep, has timed it well, but he has hit this into a stiff breeze. The ball just hangs there, and Hafeez comes around from deep midwicket. Huge cheer as Simmons walks off because the next man in is St Lucia's own Darren Sammy
flicked away with the turn, placed wide of long-on, they come back for an easy second
turning down the leg side, called a wide
doosra, but it is too short. Bravo hasn't read it, but has enough time to recover because this is short. Clears midwicket with the pull
short of a length, angling across, dabbed wide of short third man for one
tossed up on off, defended off the front foot
short of a length, turning away, beats the outside edge of the defensive bat
low full toss, hit powerfully into the leg side, beats deep square leg who is running to his left
Bravo backs away, gets a swinging low full toss, which he drives to long-on for one
bouncer outside off, dragged to deep midwicket. Keeps it down
too short for his pace. Bravo takes it from just outside off, pulls it, doesn't bother keeping it down, hits it with the wind, and eases deep square with ease
low full toss, driven to long-on for one
gets a length ball, lashes it wide of long-on for two
short of a length, no room, dabbed to point for one. The throw is wild, but they have over-run
short of a length, extra bounce, mis-hit towards deep square for one
superb shot. Ajmal stays short of a length, angling it across him, Bravo goes deep into the crease, and drives it off the back foot. Over cover it goes
quick, fast and full. Gets a single to extra cover
short of a length, pitched outside leg, worked to midwicket for one
tossed up on middle and leg, defended back to him. I think he was looking for a single to long-off, but played it too softly
big wind-up for a full ball, gets an inside edge into his boot

Afridi nearly walks the tight rope. This ball is short of a length, Bravo throws his bat at it, and the mis-hit carries to the edge of the long-on boundary. Afridi takes the catch but he is right on the edge and can't keep his balance. Steps on the rope with the ball in his hand

Bravo is down. This is quite a mean short ball. Angling in possessedly, it hits Bravo on the bicep. The bat flies out of his hand, and nearly hits the stumps. Bravo himself is down. Out comes the physio
yorker, middle and leg, Bravo makes room to play it to point for one
another good yorker, Sammy digs it back down the wicket, but it bounces over Junaid's outstretched arm for a single

that's an incredible hit. Junaid has done almost everything right. He sees Bravo backing away, and follows him with a low full toss. Bravo somehow gets enough bat on it to send it flying over extra cover for four

this is not the offbreak, and by the virtue of that it draws a massive edge on the slog, but it lands smack-bang between four men converging towards long-off. They get two while the ball is in the air
down the wicket, gets an inside edge to short fine leg
flat flat six. One of the lowest ever. Ajmal bowls flat and fast, Bravo gives it a smack towards long-off, and it goes for a six despite having hardly left ground

no calling from the fielders. Shehzad might be injured here. Bravo throws his bat at another delivery, this time he draws another massive edge that is going towards long-off. Haris from long-off and Shehzad from long-on converge without calling. Haris takes the catch with Shehzad under it. Shehzad is holding on to his left arm
doosra, short of a length, pitched outside leg, pretty quick too, deftly deflected it fine of short fine
another doosra. Pitches outside leg. Sammy leaves it on the pitch and dashes through for a single to keep strike
lovely yorker, just outside off, Sammy tries the open-face thing, but ends up digging it out back to JK

short, into the body, pulled away to deep midwicket. Sammy wants the second, and has nearly made a non-existent run. Sammy thinks he is gone, but replays show the throw was a bit full and it took Akmal a split-second extra to flick the bail off, and Sammy is super quick. In one frame his bat is on the line and the bail is coming off, but the third umpire doesn't count it as the bail fully dislodged. In the next frame, Sammy is in. He is surprised he is not out
this is to rub salt in. The yorker goes a little wrong, still pretty full, but Sammy gets enough bat under it to send it clear of long-on for six
slower short ball, Junaid has another West Indies allrounder on his backside. Sammy has been hit in the ribcage
quicker bouncer, but Sammy throws his bat at it, and ends up clearing short fine leg, and beating deep square with the pull
full, really full, but dug out to wide of long-on. Sammy rushes back for the second again

inn2.comm: short of a length, pitched outside leg, defended to leg
length ball, angling across, left alone
length ball outside off, sweetly timed to third man for one
lovely delivery. A length ball, just outside off. Shehzad can't drive because it not full enough, but he can't eave leave it because it is close to off. Then it seams away to beat the outside edge
slightly shorter, left alone outside off
full, on off, pushed between mid-off and cover for one
immediately extra pace. His the pad with a length ball before the bat comes down
more pace. Short, 148ks, into the body, Shehzad is late on the pull, but the top edge flies comfortable over the keeper for four
well in control of this pull. Short again, at 147ks, but without much sting. About chest high and outside off, and he keeps the pull down and beats square leg
length ball, angling in, 148ks, flicked to midwicket
short of a length, outside off, punched away to cover
punched away off the back foot again, wide of mid-off this time for a single
wide length ball, left alone
shimmies down the wicket a touch, sees the ball is short, punches it to point where substitute Pollard is good with the dive
short, angling in, tucked away for a single
full, just outside off, the bat face turns on the drive, and he ends up sending it back towards the stumps at the non-striker's end
short of a length, pitched outside leg, defended to leg
length ball, just outside off, defended under his head
short of a length, 148ks, on off, defended from the crease
full, into the pads, too straight and too fast. All Shehzad needs is a touch, and he gets a faint one
driven square, but straight to point
too straight again, clipped away square of long leg for a couple
yorker, 146ks, in front of off, somehow gets the bat down in time
hit him in the thigh pad or possibly even higher with a shortish quick ball, but Shehzad doesn't show any pain. He does later, only after Best has turned back
top-edged for six. It is the second such of the day. Short of a length, rising towards the armpit, Jamshed is slow into the pull, but the top edge sails over the keeper's head

leading edge this time, and it almost carries to third man. What do these batsmen carry nowadays? Bats or tree trunks? This is short of a length, he wants to work it to leg, and is done in by a bit of bounce
defended off the front foot as Holder pitches up
length ball, on off, defended off the back foot
fuller, slower, 129ks, driven to mid-off
length ball, on off, defended to cover
short of a length, on off, defended
short of a length again, seams away a touch, there is a sound as the ball passes the bat, but it is not the edge
stays short of a length, pushed wide of mid-off for one
length ball, middle and off, defended to leg
stays short of a length, just outside off, defended
full, pushed straight to Narine at mid-on, and they steal the single. Sammy is understandably displeased with that effort
overpitched on the pads, nicely clipped away for a couple
wide length ball, left alone
length ball, driven to his left, Holder sticks out the big size 15 to field
short, bounces steeply towards the chest, fends it down
short of a length, on off, stays a touch low. Defended from the crease
short, not much sting behind it, pulled away for an easy couple
short of a length, on off, pushed to point
short of a length, outside off, punched away to mid-off
Sammy is not quick enough to be bowling that short unless the bounce is spongy and steep. It's not here Only about rib high, and pulled over square leg for four
pulled away again, but to deep square for one
short of a length, outside off, dabbed away to third man
nice shot. Short of a length, angling across, punched away on the up, past Narine at mid-off, who is not the quickest in the chase. Keeps it in somehow
Narine in the firing line everywhere. Only a few metres to his right at long leg, but he doesn't reach it. Slowness personified
length ball, on off, defended
full and just outside off, driven to short cover
short of a length, middle and leg, defended to leg
full, on off, pushed to mid-off
short of a length, angling away, dabbed away to third man for one
full, on the pads, easily clipped away
length ball, on off, turns back in, defended to short midwicket
carrom ball, pitched outside leg, turns and bounces, hits him high on the pad
quick carrom ball, doesn't turn as much as expected, goes off the inside edge to fine leg
offbreak, tossed up outside leg, defended off the front foot
another offbreak, on off, pushed to short cover
short of a length, on off, defended off the back foot
stays short of a length, just outside off, punched to cover
length ball, on off, defended off the front foot
powerful cut. Not very short, but he rocks back to create the length and smashes this past point for four. If you exclude Scotland, this is Pakistan's first 50 opening in 17 games

Shehzad has sold his mate down the river. Played from deep inside the crease, he starts running for a single, only to realise he has hit it too close to Gayle at square leg. Now he sends Jamshed back, and his only chance is an error from West Indies. He almost gets it. Gayle lobs the ball back towards the non-striker's end, Sammy runs back to collect, but seems to have lost the ball. Somehow, though, the throw is a direct hit
short of a length, wide, punched away to point
offbreak, middle and leg, worked past short leg for a circle
length ball, middle and leg, defended to short leg
flighted outside off, defended off the front foot
topspinner, pitches leg, defended in front of middle
angling across him, punched to short cover
length ball, quick, doesn't turn, defended in front of off
length ball, on off, played to pint, but Hafeez doesn't respond to Shehzad's call
short of a length, angling in, defended to leg
short of a length, on off, pushed to cover
length ball, just outside off, played off the back foot to point
short of a length, outside off, bunted wide of point for a single
wide length ball, swings a little, beats his attempt to cut
length ball, middle and off, defended from the back foot

short of a length, outside off, the extra bounce beats his cut. Actually it hasn't beaten him. It has taken a thick edge, but they have not appealed. A specialist keeper would have brought the roof of the stadium off. It's Simmons keeping in the absence of the part-time wicketkeeper Johnson Charles, who is down with an upset stomach
length ball, on off, holds its line, pushed wide of point for one
dabbed away off the back foot
length ball, defended from the crease
worked around the corner for one
short of a length, outside off, dabbed to point
length ball, on off, driven to mid-off
length ball, angling in, pushed to short midwicket
short of a length, angling in, defended to short midwicket

lovely shot. Short of a length, close to him, but he uses his wrists to impart power into the cut. And Narine is beaten at third man again. Sammy is flabbergasted at Narine's effort. or lack thereof. Narine doesn't bend or dive or sprint
length all, angling in, defended off the front foot
quick ball angling across him, and beats the outside edge. Again, it seems to have taken the edge, and lodged itself in Simmons' armpit. Again no appeal
full and fast, hits the pad
inside edge and glove, but it dies before reaching the keeper
short of a length, on off, punched back to him
full on the pads, driven to long-on
full, on the pads, defended
length ball, angling in, worked away for a single
length ball, angling in, defended to short midwicket
short of a length, widish, punched away to point
short of a length, Hafeez swipes across the line, gets a massive top edge, Simmons goes back to catch it
short of a length, wide, dabbed away to third man for one
length ball, on off, defended off the front foot
flighted outside leg, defended to short leg
offbreak, defended back to him
short of a length, middle and leg, defended to short leg
short again, and defended to Pollard
short of a length, worked past short leg for one
quick length ball outside off, pretty straight, played with an open face to third man
length ball, into the pads, worked away for a single
short, waist high, but he finds deep square leg with the pull
length ball, hits the inside half of the bat as he defends
short of a length, on off, defended from the crease
short of a length, on off, defended again
length ball, angling in, clipped away for a single
flighted outside leg, worked around the corner, but can't beat square leg
offbreak, starts on leg, through Simmons too. And it's Darren Sammy whose excellent chase saves Narine a few wides. First extras of the innings
length ball, outside off, just holds its line, defended from the crease
quick offbreak, short too, cut away for a couple
flighted on the pads, flicked to short leg
flighted outside off, defended off the front foot
a flat offbreak, goes back to guide it past slip for one
short of a length, on off, defended from the crease
they are running to Gayle as if he has taken a catch. This is short and pulled, Gayle makes a regulation stop at midwicket. Sammy rushes to him to congratulate him. Jeff Dujon calls this "ridiculous"
short of a length, on off, defended back to him
slower ball, taken from outside leg, driven to long-off
short of a length, angling in defended to square leg. Shehzad wants a single, is sent back
angling in, on a length, turned to square leg
full, fast, down leg, and nicely swept away fine past short fine leg
offbreak, on off, defended back to him
flighted outside off, pushed past point for one
flat offbreak, on off, bunted wide of point for one
another quick offbreak, defended from the crease
looks to sweep from middle-stump line, gets a top edge into his pad
short of a length, angling in, hits him no the thigh pad
short of a length, outside off, pushed to point
Misbah nearly falls off from the effort of playing a defensive nudge to leg. His foot seems to be stuck in the holes, and he nearly loses balance
flicked uppishly, but wide of short midwicket
makes room to square-drive this from in front of off, but finds backward point
length ball, angling in, defended to short midwicket
full, on off, worked with the turn, wide of deep midwicket, gets a couple
short of a length, paddled away to fine leg for one
slower, offbreak, turning towards off, defended off the front foot
slightly short, he goes back to punch this, but can't beat point
fuller, middle and leg, driven back to him
this is the dart down the leg side, and has been paddled away fine of fine leg for two
short of a length, angling in, worked away to long leg
slower ball, overpitched, driven wide of mid-off. Best gives superb chase to keep them down to two
short of a length, angling in, clipped to square leg
short of a length, angling in, defended in front of leg
short of a length, angling in, and again he has found square leg

Sammy's allotment finishes with a four, which also brings up Shehzad's fifty, whose both previous fifties have been hundreds. This is a length ball into the pads, and he has almost flick-pulled through square leg for four. A short-arm jab, really
tossed up outside off, nicely worked square of square leg for one
this one doesn't turn, beats the outside edge as Shehzad defends, and off Simmons' pad it ricochets onto the off stump
driven wide of long-off
out of nowhere, without any warning, Misbah goes boom. This is full and outside of,f and he has flicked this wide of long-on, in the air
short of a length, on off, defended off the back foot
stays back to defend a quick length ball
short, wide, 138ks, really lucky that Shehzad makes no connection on this cut
not so lucky this time. This is short and wide again, at 141ks, Shehzad lets this ball have it, brandishing the bat at it with an open face. Beats third man to his left
full and straight, 142ks, overpitched. A half-volley really, and he has pushed this between the umpire and mid-on

length ball, on off, driven wide of deep cover, but the second is not on. However, Best is not at the stumps to collect the throw. Shoddy cricket. A direct hit or Best's intervention would have got Misbah here
short, not too wide, beats him on the cut
full and straight, pushed to the straight short midwicket
full, on off, defended back to him. A mini collision between the bowler and the non-striker is followed by a mock threat by Shehzad to hit Samuels with the bat. Smiles all around
softly paddled to short fine leg
short of a length, outside off, dabbed to point
sweeps a length ball from outside off, fine of deep square, comes back for two
short of a length, fired in, defended to short midwicket
short, outside off, sitting there to be cut, but it comes on slowly and Shehzad is early into the shot
short of a length, quick, but Misbah uses his pace to guide it past the diving wide slip. Sixth four off Best's bowling today
short of a length, into the ribs, defended to leg
tucked away off the hip, but there is a backward short leg in place now
bouncer, on off and middle, Misbah ducks under it
wide length ball, defended to cover--point
tucked away off the hip again, but that backward short leg is well placed
flighted on off, driven to long-off for one
makes room, then moves back to cover the stumps, and defends this to leg
flighted outside off, defended off the front foot
full and fast, driven superbly with no back-lift or follow-through. Wide of deep point it goes
tries to reverse-sweep now, but is done in by the slowness of it
short of a length, on off, defended back to him
full, on off, dug out towards short straight midwicket

Bravo takes a superb catch running back and over his shoulder. Shehzad wants to pull, but the ball is not short enough, and comes on quickly. He ends up lobbing it what seems like over mid-on, but Bravo runs back and takes it over his shoulder, never losing sight of the ball
good short delivery, rising towards the helmet from just short of a length. Misbah fends with eyes off it, and this could have flown everywhere. Falls safe, though
short of a length, just outside off, defended to short straight midwicket
short of a length, outside off, punched away to point
rising towards the chest from short of a length, Misbah rides the bounce and defends
short, wide, cut away to third man for one
big wide down the leg side
slower ball, full, played to short midwicket
gentle short ball, pulled away to deep square
full and wide, Sohail reaches out and gets an inside edge
short of a length, outside off, punched to point
fuller, angling in towards off, defended to cover
short ball from Tino, but it does no harm when it is directed down the leg side
much better, this jagged in from back of a length, was chopped towards point
shorter, he gets on his toes to guide it to gully
overpitched, Misbah slams a drive, although you would never know that with the calm manner and the lack of backlift, Gayle gets down just in time to his left at extra cover
shortish, defended off the back foot
short of a length, 139 kph, punched from the crease to point
the plan is to pepper him with short stuff, but Best has sent it down leg second time this over
short of a length again, but widish this time, and it is steered to third man
leans forward, but ends up working a full delivery straight to mid on
short ball gone wrong down the leg side, West Indies racking up the wides
and again, this was a touch fuller, but moved in down leg once more
Misbah switches on attack mode suddenly, Bravo floats up a slower length ball outside off, Misbah mows it over deep midwicket
good length into the pads, turned behind square
pushed to extra cover
pitched up delivery around off, has been smashed past the bowler, and has raced straight down the ground
hangs around the crease to a length ball that holds the line on off, and guides it to third man
good length ball around middle and leg, played out softly
short of driving length, he drops it down to point
slow bouncer, 125.7 kph, falls in front of the keeper, batsman ducks
opens the face and pushes to point
shortish delivery climbs around off stump, is guided to third man
moves across and works a length ball through square leg
pitching outside leg and going across, good length, pushed off the back foot
steers this 96 kph delivery around  off to short third, Best can't stop it
pitches this outside leg, and Sohail nudges it straight to short fine
this is pitched up, quickish, but Sohail has stayed in the crease and chopped it past point
worked to deep midwicket
angled across, but shortish, and is cut to deep point
slower ball, 116ks, on off, worked into the leg side for a single
short of a length, on off, played with an open face to point
short of a length, wide, he stands tall and punches this past point for four
down the wicket to push a length ball wide of mid-on for one
short of a length, into the body, tucked away off the hip for one
short, not too wide, steered away to third man
wide and full, driven to deep cover for one
appeal for catch the the wicket. Best finally has Misbah pulling, he thinks he has got an edge, but there isn't any. They don't review it. Rightly so
full and into the pads, flicked, but straight to midwicket
this short ball is only rib high. Pulled away for a single
short of a length, on the pads, hits the high part of the bat
that might even have been wide had Sohail not driven at it. As it turns out, his feet are rooted, and he is playing well away from his body, edging it through to the keeper
slower ball, wide, pushed to point and sets off. Akmal sends him back, and it is Akmal's call. So Misbah raises his hand and acknowledges he should have waited for the call
worked to square leg for a single
short of a length, angling in, defended to leg
wide length ball, dabbed away to third man for one
short of a length, tucked away off the hip
short of a length, outside off, holds its line, beats his outside edge, draws a half shout
short, 146ks, rib high, hurries him up in the pull. Mis-hit to midwicket
full now, at 146ks, pushed to mid-on

well done Simmons. He is actually showing he is a better keeper than Charles, except that he doesn't appeal. This is quick and down the leg side, and would have gone for four leg-byes had Simmons not dived full length
short of a length, into the pads, defended to leg
bouncer, Misbah pulls out of the pull, wants a wide for the height, but it is not called. Replays show a touch-and-go call

superb bounce for Best. From short of a length, this rises towards the chest and hits him on the bat handle. Best is right in Misbah's face. No words spoken. A maiden. Actually it has got him on the index finger of the bottom hand too
short of a length, outside off, pushed to point with an open face
smarty shot. He has seen mid-on is up in the circle, and as soon as he sees the ball is slightly full he goes over the man at mid-on. West Indies had six in the circle although the PP is over
poor fielding, this time from Samuels. A gentle nudge to long leg where Samuels comes around, but lets it through his legs. Gives it the gateway
another smart shot. A top late-cut. Waits and waits for the shortish ball to arrive, then opens the face late to send it to third man for four. Very fine
tucked away into the leg side
four leg-byes now. Samuels again. Although this one is much more difficult. Angling in, kisses the pad, goes fine, but Samuels running to his right can't keep it in
tossed up on the pads, driven to long-on for one
it's all going for Pakistan now. Misbah backs away, then comes back in front of stumps, pushes at a length ball away from the body, and gets a fine inside edge for four
he knows Narine is not turning them balls, and tries to reverse-sweep. Beaten, but this always angling across him
another delivery angled across him, defended off the back foot
another reverse, takes this from in front of leg, and guides this expertly square of short third man for four more
paddled away to fine leg from the leg-stump line
a bouncer from Best, Misbah wants a wide, but it is not called. Hard to tell because Misbah is bending a little. And he is a tall man so it would take a serious delivery to go over his head

this is getting reviewed for a strangle down the leg side. Not given out on the field. Short of a length, into the ribs, Misbah plays at it, looking to tuck it away into the leg side. The ball as it passes Misbah is awfully close to the glove. And there is a deviation. So if it has hit anything, it is the glove. The same Bravo argument in the morning should stand here. Remember we don't have HotSpot. In this case, the umpires feel there is enough doubt to not overturn the on-field call. Best and Bravo and Sammy are gutted. Best asks questions of Umpire Reiffel. Bravo stands stunned
length ball, into the pads, and he has worked away to bring up another fifty. Quiet acknowledgement of the applause follows
short of a length, towards the chest, fended to point
that's some effort from Best. This is not very short, but the ball rises towards Akmal's throats, who has to sway out of its line. Best continues to stare at him

steered away to third man. Best is not happy with something. He is arguing with Akmal. Possibly the two bumped into each other as Akmal went for the single. Tempers all over the place. It's all happening. Akmal just ran in a straight line, and Best had to steer out of the way. Akmal is in the right here
flighted outside off, Akmal stays beside the line to drive, but is beaten on the outside edge
this is the carrom ball. He has worked it against the turn, towards long-on. Looks to push for a second because he has played this with soft hands, but has to do with just the one
this is definitely not an offbreak. Is shortish, and is defended back to him
Misbah makes room, Narine follows him. Actually he beats him down the leg side

similar events to the last ball but this time the umpire doesn't call it a wide. The umpiring, I must say, has been very objectionable in this series. Misbah backs away, Narine follows him, beats him down the leg side, but is not wided
fired into the pads, worked away for one
fired in again, concedes a leg-bye
slower ball, on a length, just outside off, Akmal opens the face to guide it to the keeper on the bounce
makes room to hit this full ball to long-on. He wanted to go to off, but was cramped up for room

full-on Punjabi fight is on between Misbah and Akmal. It is not for children so I won't translate. This full toss is hit wide of long-on. Misbah wants two, Akmal doesn't come back. All hell breaks loose
AKmal makes room again, Bravo gives him none. Dug out to long-off for one
Misbah wants to go across and hit this to leg, but Bravo bowls a slower delivery, which has completely done him in. Misbah is taken by surprise completely, and doesn't even offer a shot
low full toss, Misbah moves across to work this square on the leg side for a couple
Akmal backs away, Narine tosses this up on leg, and the further turn cramps him up. Mis-hits into the leg side for a single
carrom ball. Short of a length, in front of off. Misbah defends
Narine follows the backing-away Misbah, and concedes just the single
carrom ball, but too short and too fast, and Akmal goes back to cut this clean between point and cover-point for four, using all the pace of Narine. He creates the width by backing away a little
fired in down the leg-side. Akmal has stood his ground. So a wide
flighted on off, nicely worked to deep midwicket for one
short of a length, turning in, worked into the leg side for another single

Misbah and Akmal still not running as well as they can. Misbah goes across to whip this to leg. The injured Roach runs from fine leg and shows some of his fit team-mates how to do it. He has had to run a long way and put the dive in, but they take only two runs
full and straight, nearly  yorker, dug out for one
slower ball, wide and on a length. Akmal hasn't watched it closely, and is beaten on the drive
backs away to take a full delivery from middle to push it to extra cover for one
full, nearly a yorker, Misbah can't get under it. Drives it for a single
down the wicket, but Bravo stays full and straight, and all Akmal can get is a single
Akmal makes room and swings hard at a length ball outside off. Beaten
as is Akmal. Gets a half-volley, a quick one. Akmal clears the front leg, and goes inside out to hit it over mid-off. Turns out he has hit it so well it goes for six
short. Quick and short. Akmal swings hard. Gets a top edge over the keeper's head

Akmal has played one shot too many. He has premeditated a drive, but the ball is short of a length, and all he manages is a lob to mid-off. And the covers are coming on. Forget D/L, Pakistan have lost a settled batsman who was going well to a premeditated shot. Pakistan are five ahead on D/L, though
bouncer, middle and leg. Misbah wants the wide call. Not given. It has been called one for the over. Touch and go again. Misbah has ducked a little so it is hard to tell exactly how high this is
short, rib high, pulled along the ground, past midwicket, for a couple
slower bouncer as expected. Afridi wants to ramp it over third man, but makes no connection
quicker short ball, Afridi moves across to try to drag it to leg, but is hit on the body. However, the leg-bye is taken, and Misbah is on strike now
Misbah moves across, Bravo bowls full and straight. Clipped to square leg for one

and Afridi wins the bouncer challenge. Looks like the regulation-paced one, head high, Afridi stands tall, doesn't bother transferring the weight back, and hooks. Takes the deep midwicket on, and clears him. Now less than a run a ball for Pakistan
poor bowling from Bravo. Short and wide and meek with a strong leg-side field. Afridi crunches it past point for four
short, skiddy, hits him high on the pad, but can't deny him a leg-bye
nearly that twist. Afridi attempts a cute little ramp, is beaten by a full toss. Misbah calls him through for a leg-bye, Sammy shies from square leg, misses by inches. He has gone had this hit

Misbah, you little tease. How do you even manage to do this? The game is still alive. Low full toss, hit straight down straight short midwicket's throat. Before leaving, Misbah has a word with Afridi. And also the new batsman, Ajmal
nearly another wicket. Full and straight, Ajmal is beaten, is hit on the pad outside the line of off. Wants the single but is rightly sent back
slower ball, Ajmal slogs, is beaten. The game is still alive

gets a low full toss which he has hit it straight to mid-on. Ajmal is not sure whether to go for it. Afridi wants him to. So that at least Afridi gets the strike. Pollard, though, misses the stumps from close range. And Pakistan have won 3-1
